  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering in several key ways:\n\n1. International Frameworks and Conventions\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Provide standardized approaches and principles\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries collaborate on investigations\n- Sharing evidence and intelligence\n- Extradition of financial criminals\n- Coordinated enforcement actions\n\n3. Regulatory Compliance Standards\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Due diligence protocols\n- Uniform standards across jurisdictions\n\n4. Information Sharing Mechanisms\n- International financial intelligence networks\n- Cross-border tracking of suspicious transactions\n- Coordinated monitoring of financial flows\n\n5. Enforcement Cooperation\n- Joint investigations\n- Synchronized legal strategies\n- Mutual recognition of legal proceedings\n- Consistent prosecution approaches\n\n6. Financial Sanctions\n- Targeting specific countries/entities\n- Restricting financial transactions\n- Implementing international economic penalties\n\nThese intersections create a complex, multi-layered approach to combating money laundering globally.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific aspects?",
